hall. Get this, he told them: A fiberglass cow is standing in the
middle of Michigan Avenue. Relax, the sergeant was told, the cow is
cool. ``Cows on Parade,'' a whimsical display of 300 painted and
decorated cows, has created an astonishing buzz. Sidewalk traffic
is jammed with people posing for pictures with the creatures.
Tourism has soared. Art careers have taken off. By Dirk Johnson.
