union, auto executives said. By Robyn Meredith.
</P>
<P>
   FED-RATES (Washington) _ The Federal Reserve is likely to leave
interest rates unchanged when its policy committee meets on
Tuesday, analysts and economists said. By Richard W. Stevenson.
</P>
<P>
   ITALY-TELECOM (Rome) _ Roberto Colannino, the new chairman and
chief executive of Telecom Italia, is now finding himself on the
defensive from investors who voted for his takeover proposal four
months ago. Shareholders are angry over his plan to pay for the
takeover, under which Italy's largest phone company will lose
control of its mobile unit, the company's most valuable asset. But
the Italian government, which has the power to veto such a change,
has indicated it will not intervene. By John Tagliabue.
</P>
