<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 14:06 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3350 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u s BC-BKO-MCHALE-2ND &LR;  &UR; TAKE-     10-01 0635
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKO-MCHALE-2ND </SLUG>
   TAKE-ART-BOS  
 HIBBING, Minn.: ... the way.''  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Hibbing isn't known for its basketball players. It had one of
some renown _ Dick Garmaker, a former Knick _ before McHale came
along. Agent Bill Duffy, who roomed with McHale at the University
of Minnesota, visited the city and still is amazed that it spawned
one of the 50 greatest players of all time.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was like going to another country,'' Duffy said. ``I'm
thinking, `How could this guy come from here and be this good?' I
was from east LA and I had played high school ball against (Bill)
Laimbeer and Kiki (Vandeweghe) and (David) Greenwood. I had summer
camps and stuff like that. I mean, up there, there's hardly anyone
over 6-4. It just blew my mind.'''
</P>
<P>
   McHale had three coaches going through the Hibbing public
schools _ Maciej, Knezovich, and Gary Addington. Each one shaped
him in some way, to the point where when he got to Minnesota in
1976, he was as well-schooled and polished as any freshman.
</P>
<P>
   ``I came down to the U and I was fundamentally sound. It's easy
to play when you're fundamentally sound,'' McHale said.
</P>
<P>
   Maciej, an art teacher, got the ultra-raw McHale in junior high
and marveled at his ability to have fun and still play hard. ``Once
he stepped on the floor, it was `don't mess with him.' But he
always found a way to separate the fun and the work,'' Maciej said.
He then passed McHale along to Knezovich, who had been watching
McHale for years.
</P>
<P>
   Knezovich had McHale in high school for only a year (he resigned
before the following season). But he was instrumental in teaching
McHale one of the Hall of Famer's most visible and valuable traits
_ holding the ball above his head when he got a rebound, stepping
out, and making the outlet pass.
</P>
<P>
   ``When he first started, he'd bring the ball down and I'd have
people intentionally hit him,'' Knezovich said. ``He went home
crying one day, but you know what? He learned to keep it up pretty
quick after that.'' Knezovich had another basic belief: protect the
baseline at all costs. McHale did.
</P>
<P>
   Addington had the biggest impact on McHale, so much so that
McHale chose him to be one of his presenters at the induction
ceremony. (Red Auerbach will be the other.) He had McHale for two
years and was a marked departure from the brusque, in-your-face,
post-up preferring Knezovich.
</P>
<P>
   ``He taught me more basketball than anyone else,'' McHale said
of Addington, who took McHale's senior-year team to the state
final, where it lost in the title game. ``I learned how to play
under him. We did a ton of drill work. You learned how to play the
whole game, not just one role. That served me for my whole
career.''
</P>
<P>
   Addington stayed at Hibbing for 13 years then moved on to
Rochester, where he oversees athletics at the city's three schools.
He and McHale have remained close socially, and he, too, has his
own cache of McHale stories, such as the one where McHale stayed on
the team bus and ended up going out to dinner with the bus driver
instead of being at the gym, ready to play.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't take a whole lot of credit for Kevin,'' he said. ``I
think I've been the primary beneficiary of our relationship. By the
end of his senior year, I knew he'd be a great college player. I
could see that. And after a year and a half at the U, I could see
he'd get to the next level.''
</P>
<P>
   He went there and beyond, which is why Addington and Maciej were
part of the Hibbing-related contingent that made the trip to
Springfield. The group also included brother John and his family,
and McHale's mother. Friends like Duffy, `Bones,' and Big Joe also
are in town. Springfield may never recover.
</P>
<P>
   The Beanhead came, too, so the dock will have to wait a little
longer. After all, the house apparently isn't going anywhere
anytime soon.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
