executive, Carly Fiorina, tells analysts that the company has a
``decent shot'' at meeting fourth-quarter earnings estimates, but
that sales growth would be at the low end of estimated ranges. She
also announces some management changes.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ At 12:50 p.m., stocks are modestly lower.
The Dow Jones industrial average was down 110 points, the S&AMP;P 500
down 10 points and the Nasdaq composite down 23 points. The 30-year
bond yield was 6.15 percent. European markets were also lower, with
London down 0.85 percent and Frankfurt 0.86 percent. In Japan, the
Nikkei closed up 0.65 percent, while the Hong Kong market was
closed in observance of the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
People's Republic of China. The dollar stood at 105.6 yen.
</P>
