summit by calling on all states to emphasize strategies for
``improving teacher quality, providing all students a fair
opportunity to meet higher standards, and holding schools
accountable for results.'' The more than 100 leaders at the summit
came from governments, companies and organizations that supply more
than 90 percent of the money, teachers and administrators in public
schools. (Mollison, Cox Service).
