<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SUNDAY-$ADV03-BUDGET-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  
 For Release SUNDAY, October 3, 1999
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following FEATURE stories, in
advance, for use by NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LIFESTYLE &LR;   &UR; (l) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HANDYMAN-HOTTON (Undated) _ A sliver of cedar shingle that comes
off can be glued or nailed back. By Peter Hotton.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   WARSH-COLUMN (Undated) _ David Warsh writes on economic topics
for The Boston Globe.
</P>
<P>
   FINANCE-HOOKER (Undated) _ If inflation averages 3.5 percent,
after 19 years aninvestor will need $56,152 to buy the same goods
and services that $29,208 buys today. By Kenneth Hooker.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
