<P>
   COMPUTER-COLUMN (Undated) _ The computer mouse has come a long
way, baby, since Douglas Englebart's first model, invented in 1963
as a simple wooden shell on wheels. When it was finally patented in
1970, it was given the catchy name of ``X-Y Position Indicator for
a Display System.'' Today, mice are the primary way folks interact
with their PCs, thanks to graphical interfaces and Web browsers. A
look at two new examples of Mouse evolution. By DWIGHT SILVERMAN.
