U.S. government are betting that helping Orguste Boniface and his
neighbors sell their best coffee directly to American buyers will
put more cash in the farmers' pockets. In doing so, the cash may
give this stricken country its best, perhaps last, shot at staying
afloat. By DUDLEY ALTHAUS. (Filed Thursday. Graphic available on
NYT database.)
