committed during the day of the anniversary. (Kunstel/Albright, Cox
News Service).
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-DUMPING _ UM ITOOT, West Bank _ For months, toxins oozed
out of rusting barrels stacked in low valley of olive trees and
small houses. Contrary to the law, they were delivered by an
Israeli, welcomed by a Palestinian and highlighted the nearly
uncontrolled dumping of waste in the West Bank. The barrels were
removed this week. But, it was just the latest incident that
threatened the groundwater supplies for both Israelis and
Palestinians. Now, with peace talks warming up, officials are
trying to find ways to stop the polluting that has become common
place while the land has been under dispute. (Kaplow, Cox News
Service). WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving spot on Friday, Oct. 1
</P>
