should the Kansas company merge with MCI-WorldCom. Also checking to
how the market treats BellSouth's stock today. (Kannell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   NORFOLK _ ATLANTA Norfolk Southern said it's selling its office
buildings and other property in Atlanta as part of an ongoing
evaluation of its real-estate holdings. It railroad hired
Insignia/ESG Inc., a unit of New York-based Insignia Financial
Group Inc., to handle the sales. The properties include 404,020
square feet of office space in four buildings. The buildings house
1,500 workers in departments including accounting, customer
service, engineering and information technology. (Salter, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WAFFLEHOUSE-RACISM _ Another Waffle house franchisee is hit with
another racial discrimination lawsuit. A group of five African
Americans are suing the franchisee _ the largest in the system _
alleging they were refused service because they are black.
</P>
<P>
   We take a look at the case. (Poole, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   INTERFACE _ Followup on Interface/interview with CFO. The stock
dropped 29 percent last week after the company said it wouldn't
meet 3Q earnings forecasts. What's the carpet maker doing to
overcome its Wall Street troubles, and how will it regroup after
the loss of COO Charlie Eitel? (Bond, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   COX-MP3 _ ATLANTA _ MP3radio.com, a division of Cox Interactive,
names a programming director. We take the opportunity to update
readers on what's happening with this new outfit. (Haddad, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WEATHERCHANNEL _ The Weather Channel plans to pump television
programming to Time Warner cable system in Memphis via the
Internet. That's a first for the industry. The content will be
local weather and air on a separate, new channel. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
