<P>
   FLEET-BOARD (Boston) _ Fleet names the members of its
post-BankBoston merger board of directors and it reflects who's
calling the shots at the reorganized bank. By Lynnley Browning. 900
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS (Foxborough, Mass.) -- There's probably a good
chance Dave Wohlabaugh wasn't shaking in his boots in Cleveland
this week, but he probably got a good laugh from the phone messages
Chad Eaton was leaving him. By Nick Cafardo. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-BRUINS (Boston) _ Steve Heinze has bounced back and forth
from left wing to right, from a boat load of ice time to a few
shifts here and there. By Nancy Marrapese-Burrell. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-REDSOX-ORIOLES (Baltimore) _ By Michael Madden.
</P>
<P>
   BKO-RYAN-COLUMN (Springfield, Mass.) _ By Bob Ryan.
</P>
<P>
   MCDONOUGH-COLUMN (Undated) _ Harry Sinden has a deal for Byron
Dafoe. Not a trade. A deal. By Will McDonough.
</P>
