Accompanies CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   AT A GLANCE: 2000 Chevrolet Suburban/Yukon XL
</P>
<P>
   The Package: Full-size, four-door, five- to nine-passenger, V-8
powered, rear- or four- wheel-drive sport-utility wagons.
</P>
<P>
   Highlights: GM has completely updated the venerable Suburban for
2000, based on the chassis and appearance of the new full-size
Chevy Silverado and GMC Sierra pickups introduced last year.
Everything is new, including the engines. And for the first time,
the GMC version is not called Suburban; it is now the Yukon XL.
</P>
<P>
   Negatives: The electric-window buttons, on the door armrests,
are too sensitive; they are accidentally triggered just by hands
casually resting on the armrests.
</P>
<P>
   Major competitors: Ford Excursion, Ford Expedition/Lincoln
Navigator, Toyota Land Cruiser/Lexus LX 470, Range Rover.
</P>
<P>
   EPA fuel economy: Not available.
</P>
<P>
   Base price range: No prices announced yet, but they are expected
to be close to last year's prices.
</P>
<P>
   On The Road rating: A-plus.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
</P>
