<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, OCTOBER 2
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-YUGOSLAVIA-POLITICS-NYT (moved on Thursday, Sept. 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Sept.
30, about protests in Belgrade against President Slobodan Milosevic
of Yugoslavia misstated the surname of an aide to the opposition
leader Zoran Djindjic in some copies. The aide is Cedmoir
Jovanovic, not Jankovic.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SENSATIONS-REVIEW-NYT (moved on Thursday, Sept. 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Sept.
30, about ``Sensation: Young British Artists From the Saatchi
Collection,'' at the Brooklyn Museum of Art, gave a misspelled
surname in some copies for an artist whose portrait of an English
murderer is in the show. He is Marcus Harvey, not Heavey.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-KIDS-MUSIC-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Sept. 22)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Sept.
22, gave an erroneous price supplied by the publisher, GVOX for
Learn to Play Music With Ricky Recorder. It costs $49.99, not
$59.99.
</P>
</TEXT>
