<HEADLINE>
GAILEY: MCIVER WON'T PLAY TOMORROW
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Cowboys coach Chan Gailey officially ruled guard
Everett McIver (hamstring) out of tomorrow's game against the
Arizona Cardinals yesterday, but said that decisions on cornerback
Kevin Smith (back) and tackle Erik Williams (quad) won't be made
until right before the kickoff.
</P>
<P>
   Reserve guard Tony Hutson has been taking all the snaps this
week at right guard and will start in place of McIver.
</P>
<P>
   The decision on Williams could have the most impact for the
Cowboys. Though he is listed as probable for the game, he has not
taken many snaps in practice. Rookie Solomon Page got all the work
with the first-team offense yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   Gailey said it was crucial for Page to get the repetitions in
practice. If Williams can't play, the Cowboys will at least have
the comfort of knowing they did everything they could to get Page
ready for a possible matchup with Cardinals defensive end Andre
Wadsworth.
</P>
<P>
   One of the factors in the game-day decision on Williams is
whether he can be more effective hobbled against the speedy
Wadsworth than an inexperienced Page.
</P>
<P>
   Gailey said Smith had a good day of practice yesterday for the
third consecutive day. If he plays, he would back up Kevin Mathis
at left cornerback. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
